<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1785,2035]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,327,1971,1997]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species uniquely possesses a thick and short ductus bursae in the female genitalia and strong thornlike cornuti in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
